                    <span class="opener__topics  -is-over-bg opener__topics--dark">
            <a class="opener__topics-link  -is-over-bg opener__topics-link--dark" href="https://www.propublica.org/topics/environment">Environment</a>
        </span>
    
    <h1 class="opener__hed  -is-over-bg opener__hed--dark opener__hed--small" >        The American Oil Industry’s Playbook, Illustrated: How Drillers Offload Costly Cleanup Onto the Public
    </h1>

            <h2 class="opener__dek  -is-over-bg opener__dek--dark"  >            Oil executive Tom Ragsdale walked away from his old wells, making the pollution left behind the state of New Mexico’s problem. His tactics, however, are ubiquitous in the industry.
        </h2>
    
            <div class="article-meta-1  -is-over-bg article-meta-1--dark">
            <span class="article-meta-1__byline">
                by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/mark-olalde">Mark Olalde</a>, illustrations by <span class="name">Peter Arkle</span>, special to <a href="https://www.propublica.org">ProPublica</a>            </span>
            <time class="article-meta-1__pubdate">
                <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-12-30EST05:00">Dec. 30, 2024, 5 a.m. EST</time>
            </time>
        </div>
    
    </div> <!-- Close .opener__topic-title-dek-wrapper -->

    
</div>
        
