                    />

            
    
<figcaption class="attribution">
    
    
    
    </figcaption>

</figure>

        
    
                    
<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="32.0">Regulators will likely grow tired of asking you to clean up your wells, but you can make the case for leaving them unplugged for now. Pitch grand plans, as other drillers have — maybe <a href="https://penncapital-star.com/energy-environment/in-rural-pennsylvania-crypto-mining-offers-a-lifeline-for-dying-gas-wells/">repurposing the wells for bitcoin mining</a>, <a href="https://undark.org/2024/03/26/carbon-storage-abandoned-wells/">carbon sequestration</a> or <a href="https://www.alicat.com/support/gold-hydrogen/">the synthesis of hydrogen fuel</a> — that require the wells to remain open.</p>
        
    
                    

<figure
    data-pp-id="33"
    data-pp-blocktype="image"
    class="bb-image size08 center  wide-sm wrap 
                ">

    


                    
    


    <img
        class=""
        alt=""
