                    />

            
    
<figcaption class="attribution">
    
    
    
    </figcaption>

</figure>

        
    
                    
<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="44.0">Now that you’ve offloaded your wells, you’re free to start fresh — launch a new oil company and buy some of your old wells for pennies on the dollar, <a href="https://www.propublica.org/article/the-rising-cost-of-the-oil-industrys-slow-death">a proven option</a>. Maybe you leave oil entirely — <a href="https://www.propublica.org/article/oklahoma-oil-cleanup">that’s also tried-and-true</a>. Or become a vintner and open a winery just down the road from the wells you left as orphans — <a href="https://www.desertsun.com/in-depth/news/environment/2021/06/25/oil-bankruptcies-leave-environment-cleanup-california-taxpayers/4977647001/">you wouldn’t be the first</a>.</p>
        
    
                    

<figure
    data-pp-id="45"
    data-pp-blocktype="image"
    class="bb-image size08 center  wide-sm wrap 
                ">

    


                    
    


    <img
        class=""
