                    />

            
    
<figcaption class="attribution">
    
    
    
    </figcaption>

</figure>

        
    
                    
<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="58.0">The State Land Office estimated that cleaning up that site alone would cost about $1 million.</p>
        
    
                    
<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="59.0">In 2020, New Mexico <a href="https://www.documentcloud.org/documents/25141647-2020-09-01-judgment">won a judgment against Ragsdale’s companies</a> that, with interest, is now worth more than $3.5 million. But it won’t cover the cleanup cost. Between a small bond and the judgment, the state has been able to recover a mere $50,000 or so from Siana and related entities.</p>
        
    
                    

<figure
    data-pp-id="60"
    data-pp-blocktype="image"
    class="bb-image size08 center  wide-sm wrap 
                ">

    


                    
    


