    <div class="story-card__description">
                
        <h3 class="story-card__hed" >
            <a href="https://www.propublica.org/article/north-dakota-ethics-commission-legislature-restrictions">
                                    “BadAss Grandmas” Pushed for an Ethics Commission. Then the North Dakota Legislature Limited Its Power.
                            </a>
        </h3>

        <p class="story-card__dek" >
                            Led by a bipartisan group of women, North Dakotans voted to create an ethics oversight body six years ago. Since then, the group has received 81 complaints and has not substantiated a single one.
                    </p>

        <p class="story-card__byline">
            by <a class="name" href="https://northdakotamonitor.com/author/jacob-orledge/">Jacob Orledge</a>, <a href="https://northdakotamonitor.com/">North Dakota Monitor</a>,             <time class="timestamp" datetime="2025-01-06EST06:00">Jan. 6, 6 a.m. EST</time>
        </p>

                <p class="story-card__unit">Local Reporting Network</p>
            </div>
</div>
                            </div>
            </ol> <!-- end .most-read-group -->

</div> <!-- end .most-read -->



    
